Cardiff are considering bringing in Glenn Roeder as part of their management team. 

The club want Leyton Orient boss Russell Slade as manager with Roeder as technical director. 

Slade is the favourite to take over at the Bluebirds after the club parted company with Ole Gunnar Solskjaer last week. 

Glenn Roeder is wanted as a technical director at Cardiff 

Owner Vincent Tan wants Leyton Orient boss Russell Slade to replace Ole Gunnar Solskjaer 

The Orient boss was looking like being sacked a few weeks ago by the club's chairman Francesco Becchetti but he has since rejected an approach from Cardiff to talk to the former Yeovil boss. 

Cardiff's miserable run of form continued as they were dumped out of the Capital One Cup. losing 3-0 at home to Bournemouth. 

They are languishing 16th in the Championship and owner Vincent Tan will want to appoint Solskjaer's replacement as soon as possible.  

